race.comment: ME STYLE (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (19.10) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Form at the trip sound including two wins. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Has ability and can bounce back. COPERNICUS (3) slotted in just off the lead from the wide draw last start and boxed on to finish second (18.64) at this track in a Grade 5 over 318m. The form from his last run stacks up well. Expected to be in the finish again. EXPLODE OPAL (8) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by half a length at this track in a handy 18.61 beating Mobile Glass. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Capable of going well again. PASS THE GLASS (1) is fresh from a short break and ready to run well.
